reviews.review_text: Classic Dead Great recording of a classic 76 outing. Truly excellent H/S!/F

Super-Fine Work, Mr. Dusborne... Thank you for taking the time to make this. 
It is the 08-04 feature show at #DeadOnThisDate on twitter.

Fractalicious As of 2018, this is the definitive version of the show.

kevin tobin's sbd has a bit higher quality sound than this one, but the crowd energy and how it fuels the band and vice versa, it's quite a thing to hear.

Scarlet begonias and slipknot are among the finest versions i've ever heard so far. 

Judging from the heady version ratings of this show's songs, it certainly feels incredibly underrated.

Lucky ye who stumble upon it at some point in time during your brief tenure as sentient organics.

still the definitive version of the show in 2023 Phil's bass is a bit overwhelming, but here, if you love Phil Lesh, is a treasure of a show! Great playing throughout, that gut-shaking bass throughout, but not so overwhelming that the rest of the band is not audible---this one is definitely one NOT TO MISS! The fifteen-minute Scarlet Begonias is standout too, but followed immediately by the 29:47 POWERFUL version of Help > Slip > Frank, one of the best ever recorded, this show is among my top couple of dozen Dead shows ever.
  --Check it out! As the possibly late (?) and great reviewer, 'Doctor Flashback' would have advised-- 'Don't Miss This'!!!
